Usage: addDummyBoundaryWires [-help] -layers <string> [-shape <string>]
                             [-shortWires <string>] [-space <string>] [-masks <string> ]

-help                                # Prints out the command usage
-layers <string>                     # Specify one or multiple layers to add
                                     # dummy wires. (string, required)
-masks <string>                      # Specify one or multiple mask number
                                     # which short dummy boundary wires snap
                                     # to. The number of specified mask values
                                     # should match the number of specified
                                     # layers in option layers. (string, optional)
-shape <string>                      # Specify shape of dummy wires,
                                     # default=None. (string, optional)
-shortWires <string>                 # Specify one or multiple set of length of
                                     # short dummy boundary wires and space
                                     # between them. The number of specfied
                                     # shortWires values should be twice of the
                                     # number of specified layers in option
                                     # layers. (string, optional)
-space <string>                      # Specify one or multiple space values to
                                     # design boundary, default=0. The number
                                     # of specified space values should match
                                     # the number of specified layers in option
                                     # layers. (string, optional)